ontalcini had been the oldest living <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize\" title=\"Nobel Prize\">Nobel<\/a> laureate and was the first ever to reach a 100th birthday.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rita100_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Rita_Levi-Montalcini#cite_note-Rita100-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> On 22 April 2009, she was feted with a 100th birthday party at <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Rome\" title=\"Rome\">Rome<\/a>'s city hall.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ibro_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Rita_Levi-Montalcini#cite_note-ibro-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-excelle_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Rita_Levi-Montalcini#cite_note-excelle-5\"><span>[<\/span>5<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Rita Levi-Montalcini","place_of_birth":"Turin ,  Italy","place_of_death":"Rome ,  Italy","text":"Rita Levi-Montalcini ,  born in Italy , Physiology or Medicine, 1986","year":1986.0}